<encodingDesc n="1.5">
<projectDesc><p>This transcription was made by the Verbum Project between 2004 and 2008 as part of an online and printed edition of the Old Latin versions of John.</p></projectDesc>
<editorialDecl><p>This transcription covers <locus>extracts of ff. 6r, 6v, 7r, 8v, 11r</locus>. Only the text of John in the canon tables has been transcribed. However, because of the repetition of verses, the page breaks in this transcription relate to the chapter breaks of John rather than the pagination of the manuscript.The transcription includes the text of John from the canon tables for collation purposes. The initial transcription file was a plain text file for use with COLLATE. Further information about the procedures followed may be found in the electronic edition at <ptr target="http://www.iohannes.com/vetuslatina/"/></p>
<p>This second edition of the file was converted to XML by Catherine Smith using the project's Python conversion scripts 1.0.</p>
<p>The XML specifications used are version 1.5 of the IGNTP Guidelines available at <ptr target="http://epapers.bham.ac.uk/1892/"/></p></editorialDecl></encodingDesc>

